Sentencas: A BaFe0.9Zr0.1O3-delta (BFZ) is successfully synthesized and its characteristics are investigated.
Titulo: Zr doped BaFeO3-δ as a robust electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxide exhibits high stability and a cubic perovskite structure in a reducing atmosphere.
Titulo: Zr doped BaFeO3-δ as a robust electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) supported symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with BFZ electrode demonstrates a maximum power density of 1097 mW cm(-2) using humidified H-2 as the fuel and ambient air as the oxidant at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Zr doped BaFeO3-δ as a robust electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: And as low as 0.190 Omega cm(2) of polarization resistance of single cell is observed at 650 degrees C. Moreover, the electrode demonstrates high stability in 100 h test, as well as redox stability in both oxidizing and reducing atmospheres.
Titulo: Zr doped BaFeO3-δ as a robust electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The high electrochemical property and good stability suggest that the BFZ is promising candidate for symmetrical SOFC electrode.
Titulo: Zr doped BaFeO3-δ as a robust electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells
